topic.title: Partition Setting Block

body.p: This block contains the fields that are used to configure a partition. An instance of this block is created for each desired partition. The number of supported partitions cannot change dynamically during run time. So, the Configuration File defines the number of partitions to be used after boot.

The settings define whether the partition is valid, and set the MPS for all switch ports in the partition. They also specify how many ports the partition contains, the USP port mode, and other partition settings.
